# 2. JavaScript Frontend Monitoring

Install Browser SDK:

```bash
npm install @datadog/browser-rum
```

### RUM (Real User Monitoring)

```javascript
import { datadogRum } from '@datadog/browser-rum';

datadogRum.init({
  applicationId: 'APP_ID',
  clientToken: 'CLIENT_TOKEN',
  site: 'datadoghq.com',
  service: 'frontend-app',
  env: 'production',
  sampleRate: 100,
  trackInteractions: true
});
```

Track user actions:

```javascript
datadogRum.addAction(
  'checkout_button_clicked'
);
```

Track errors:

```javascript
try {
   processOrder();
}
catch(error){
   datadogRum.addError(error);
}
```

Captured:

* Page load time
* User clicks
* JavaScript errors
* Session recordings
* Frontend latency

